commands.description:
The ExecuteJs command accepts two arguments:
Property Key - Used to identify the locator of the specific web element on which the action will be performed.
JS Script Key - Used to reference the JavaScript script that will be executed in the browser.
The command uses a JSON input parameter to pass the required data for execution.

Input Param JavaScript ::
{
  "scripts": {
    "scrollToElement-1": [
      {
        "script": "document.getElementsByClassName('slick-viewport')[3].scrollBy(100, (document.getElementsByClassName('slick-viewport')[3].scrollHeight / 100) * 100)"
      }
    ]
  }
}

